<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Privacy Policy - Event Management Website</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
            background: linear-gradient(to bottom, #ff7f50, #87ceeb, #ffb6c1, #90ee90);
            color: #fff;
            transition: background 0.5s ease;
        }
        .container {
            max-width: 1100px;
            margin: 50px auto;
            padding: 20px;
            background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8);
            border-radius: 10px;
            transition: transform 0.3s ease;
            box-shadow: 0 2px 4px rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.2);
        }
        h2, h3 {
            color: rgb(118, 118, 252);
            font-size: 30px;
        }
        h1 {
            color: #FFC107;
            font-size: 40px;
            text-align: center;
        }
        p {
            line-height: 1.6;
            font-size: 20px;
        }
        ul {
            list-style-type: disc;
            margin-left: 20px;
            font-size: 18px;
        }
        a {
            color: #FFC107;
            text-decoration: none;
            transition: color 0.3s ease;
        }
        a:hover {
            color: #FF4500;
        }
        .container:hover {
            transform: translateY(-5px);
        }
        .container:hover p, .container:hover h2, .container:hover h3, .container:hover h1 {
            color: #FF4500;
        }
        .container:hover ul {
            color: #FF4500;
        }
        .container p:hover {
            color: #00FFFF;
        }
        .container h2:hover, .container h3:hover, .container h1:hover {
            color: #00FFFF;
        }
        .container ul li:hover {
            color: #00FFFF;
        }
        body:hover {
            background: linear-gradient(to bottom, #7FFFD4, #FFD700, #00FA9A, #FF69B4);
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

    <div class="container">
        <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
        <p>This Privacy Policy governs the manner in which our event management website collects, uses, maintains, and discloses information collected from users (each, a "User") of the website.</p>
    
        <h2>1. Personal Identification Information</h2>
        <p>We may collect personal identification information from Users in a variety of ways, including, but not limited to, when Users visit our site, register on the site, fill out a form, respond to a survey, and in connection with other activities, services, features, or resources we make available on our site.</p>
    
        <h2>2. Non-personal Identification Information</h2>
        <p>We may collect non-personal identification information about Users whenever they interact with our site. Non-personal identification information may include the browser name, the type of computer, and technical information about Users' means of connection to our site, such as the operating system and the Internet service providers utilized and other similar information.</p>
    
        <h2>3. Web Browser Cookies</h2>
        <p>Our site may use "cookies" to enhance User experience.</p>
    
        <h2>4. Introduction</h2>
        <p>Welcome to [Your Event Management Website] (the "Website"). We are committed to protecting your privacy and personal information. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, disclose, and safeguard your information when you visit our website.</p>
    
        <h2>5. Information We Collect</h2>
        <p>We may collect personal information that you voluntarily provide to us when you:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Register for an account</li>
            <li>Make a reservation or purchase tickets</li>
            <li>Subscribe to our newsletter</li>
            <li>Contact us via email or through our website</li>
        </ul>
        <p>This information may include your name, email address, phone number, billing address, and any other information you choose to provide.</p>
    
        <h2>6. How We Use Your Information</h2>
        <p>We may use the information we collect from you to:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Provide, operate, and maintain our website</li>
            <li>Process transactions and fulfill orders</li>
            <li>Send you promotional communications</li>
            <li>Respond to your inquiries and provide customer support</li>
            <li>Improve our website and marketing efforts</li>
            <li>Comply with legal and regulatory requirements</li>
        </ul>
    
        <h2>7. Information Sharing</h2>
        <p>We may share your information with:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Service providers who assist us in operating our website</li>
            <li>Third-party vendors who help us manage and analyze data</li>
            <li>Legal and regulatory authorities when required by law</li>
        </ul>
        <p>We will not sell, rent, or disclose your personal information to third parties without your consent, except as described in this Privacy Policy.</p>
    
        <h2>8. Security</h2>
        <p>We take reasonable measures to protect the information we collect from unauthorized access, use, and disclosure. However, please be aware that no method of transmission over the internet or electronic storage is 100% secure.</p>
    </div>
</body>
</html>
